Nothing wrong with this. Listening to it at the moment and it seems fine to me. Thanks for sharing and seeding.

In response to Phykix comment, I also think it a grievous insult to us downloaders of free music that the uploader did not take the time to hop in his time machine to October 25, 1968, grab Jimi Hendrix himself, and take him back in time to record 'All Along the Watchtower', and then fit it into this album, which was released on May 12, 1967. Of course, you would also have to grab a copy of Bob Dylan's single, 'All Along the Watchtower' before you went, because it wasn't released until November 6, 1967.

A better question would be, why did Jimi insult us by not recording a cover of a song that hadn't even yet been conceived, and release it on this album? What a jerk.
